# 4. Database Ownership Model

```text
Clinic

├── Staff

│     ├── Doctor

│     └── Receptionist

├── Patients

├── Queue Entries

├── Visits

├── Treatment Plans

├── Appointments

├── Prescriptions

├── Payments

├── XRays

└── Audit Logs
```

Everything belongs to a clinic.

---

# 5. Authorization Rules

Never authorize using:

```text
dentist_id
```

Use:

```text
clinic_id
+
role
```

Repository methods automatically scope by clinic.

---

# 6. AI Pipeline

Doctor Flow:

```text
Audio

↓

SarvamProvider

↓

Transcript

↓

GeminiProvider

↓

consultation.schema

↓

medicine.parser

↓

TransactionService.completeConsultation()

↓

Database
```

Reception Flow:

```text
Audio

↓

SarvamProvider

↓

Transcript

↓

Queue Entry
```

No AI diagnosis.

---

# 7. Transaction Service

Create orchestration methods:

* createClinic()
* joinClinic()
* completeConsultation()
* completeCheckout()
* recordPayment()
* createTreatmentPlan()

Multi-table operations must happen here.

---

# 8. Repository Pattern

Controllers:

* validate
* call service
* return response

Repositories:

* own all Supabase access

Example:

```text
findById(id, clinicId)

findAll(clinicId)

create(data)

update(id, clinicId)

softDelete(id, clinicId)
```

---

# 9. Validation

Use Zod.

No:

```javascript
...req.body
```

Explicit field whitelisting only.

---

# 10. API Response Standard

Success:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {}
}
```

Failure:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "details": {}
  }
}
```

No silent mock responses.

---

# 11. AI Provider Rules

Providers:

* Sarvam
* Gemini
* Mock

Mock provider:

Development only.

Production startup should fail if API keys are missing.

Validate:

* GEMINI_API_KEY
* SARVAM_API_KEY
* SUPABASE_URL
* SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
* JWT_SECRET

---

# 12. Medicine Schema

Canonical schema:

```json
{
  "name": "",
  "strength": "",
  "frequency": "",
  "duration": "",
  "mealTiming": "",
  "instructions": ""
}
```

All AI outputs pass through:

```text
medicine.parser.js
```

---

# 13. Queue Flow

```text
Waiting

↓

Checked In

↓

In Consultation

↓

Ready For Checkout

↓

Completed
```

Reception owns queue state.

Doctor never manually changes queue state.

---

# 14. Consultation Flow

```text
Doctor Save

↓

TransactionService.completeConsultation()

├── Create Visit

├── Create Treatment Plan

├── Create Prescription

├── Create Suggested Appointments

├── Update Queue

└── Audit Log
```

Appointments are created with:

```text
status = suggested
```

Reception confirms them later.

---

# 15. Payment Flow

```text
Reception

↓

recordPayment()

↓

Payment Transaction

↓

Update Treatment Plan Totals

↓

Audit Log
```

Use transactions.

---

# 16. Soft Delete

Use:

```text
deleted_at

deleted_by
```

Repositories automatically exclude deleted records.

---

# 17. Audit Logs

Track:

* CREATE
* UPDATE
* DELETE
* PAYMENT
* PRESCRIPTION
* ROLE CHANGE
* QUEUE REORDER

Audit failure must never fail the business operation.

---

# 18. Logging

Use:

```text
requestId

clinicId

staffId

route

duration
```

No scattered console.log.

---

# 19. Performance

* Pagination everywhere
* Batch queries
* No N+1
* Stream file uploads
* Add indexes
* Queue tokens via DB sequence

